## Context

- Phase 1 complete: 20 genes curated, 16 strong/moderate
- Phase 1b complete: Costa Rica IBD + clinical exome cross-validation. 13/20 multi-stream convergence.
- Phase 2 complete: gnomAD v4 constraint analysis. Both sets enriched for LoF-intolerant genes.
- Phase 3 complete (task #585): STRING v12 PPI network (37 nodes, 44 edges). Permutation tests NOT significant (cross-edge p=0.96, proximity p=0.23) — rare/GWAS genes form distinct modules. Convergence is modular via bridge genes: CREBBP (chromatin→TF), DLG4 (synaptic→GWAS), GRIN2B, NOTCH1, LATS1. Mechanism predictions for PPP5C (phosphatase/dopamine), EXOC1 (vesicle trafficking), GXYLT1 (Notch glycosylation).
- Phase 4 complete (task #586): Pathway convergence analysis. 11 convergent pathways (combined p<0.01) — TARGET MET. Top: neuronal system (p=2.1e-5), nervous system dev (p=2.9e-5), synaptic transmission (p=6.1e-5), dopaminergic synapse (p=2.2e-4). All CSTC-relevant. Hippo pathway includes WWC1+NDFIP2.
- Remaining: task #587 (Phase 5 — cross-disorder specificity, priority 3). Depends on Phase 3+4 (now complete).
